Sesona Ngqakamba Police are monitoring the group of protesters in Mothibaskraal, near Mankweng. (File, News24) Multimedia    ·   User Galleries   ·   News in Pictures
	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories Residents of Mothibaskraal, near Mankweng outside Polokwane, took to the streets on Monday morning to protest against the non-delivery of water tanks in their community. The disgruntled group blockaded parts of the R71 road with tree branches. ALSO READ: 2 police vehicles torched in Bot River protest Polokwane police spokesperson Colonel Moatshe Ngoepe said officers were on the ground monitoring the group. Ngoepe said there hadn't been any violence so far, and that traffic was flowing despite the protest action. Residents are reportedly accusing the Polokwane Municipality of failing to deliver water tanks to them. ALSO READ: Two major national routes remain closed due to protest action Polokwane Municipality spokesperson Matshidiso Mothapo said they were aware of the community's concerns regarding water tanks, and that they had scheduled a meeting with them for later on Monday. "We have a meeting scheduled today with the ward councillor and the community reps with regards to the issue with water tankers, which is what we will try to understand when we get there," Mothapo said.     24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  